cerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe parable of the miser and the spender is that of two men clad in armor from their chests to their collars. As for the spender, he does not spend but that it extends or broadens over his\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":37966,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2022\/07\/18\/tasbeeh-daily\/","url_meta":{"origin":40703,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Tasbih: Glorifying Allah daily erases many sins","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 18, 2022","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever declares the glory of Allah and His praises one hundred times in a day, his sins will be diminished even if they are like the foam of the sea.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 6405, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":40707,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/07\/07\/munafiq-lost-in-kufr\/","url_meta":{"origin":40703,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Nifaq: Hypocrites are lost wandering in unbelief","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 7, 2023","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe parable of the hypocrite is that of a sheep wandering from flock to flock. It